Hashtable Java ka ek purana (legacy) Map implementation hai jo key-value pairs store karta hai — bilkul HashMap jaisa…
par ek twist ke saath:

👉 Ye synchronized hota hai (thread-safe by default)
Basic rules
Duplicate keys ❌
Duplicate values ✅
No null key ❌
No null value ❌
Order maintain nahi hota ❌
Time complexity ≈ O(1)

Ek line me samajh:
HashMap = fast, not thread-safe
Hashtable = thread-safe, but old + slow